connectorBean.name: MyAccts Employee Load
connectorBean.description: CSV import of the MyAccts employees

property.name: attributesColumnsName
property.description: Names of the columns of the CSV divided by separator ( Ex. ID,NAME,GIVENNAME ). Set it to EXTERNALFILE, to use the file descriptor.

property.name: csvSeparator
property.description: Enter the symbol representing the separator

property.name: pathFile
property.description: Enter the directory where are the csv files to read

property.name: attributesColumnsNameFileDescriptor
property.description: Path file that contains the column names of CSV divided by separator

property.name: ignoreFirstLine
property.description: If the csv file contains the header value set "true" otherwise "false"

property.name: ATTRIBUTE_NAME_TO_DENORMALIZE
property.description: Attribute name to be used for the target events de-normalization. If it is not set, there will be no de-normalization.

property.name: csvOrder
property.description: Enter the csv order mode: sort by '1' Filename, '2' Size, '3' Date, '4' Type The default sorting method is by Name Negative mode means descending sort

property.name: writeMode
property.description: Enter the write mode: 'append' to modify the same file each event or 'write' create a new file each event.
